The article discusses the new actions taken by the United States to restrict Iran's nuclear, ballistic missile, and conventional weapons pursuits. The Trump Administration has issued a new Executive Order that restores United Nations sanctions on Iran and imposes new sanctions and export controls on entities and individuals supporting Iran's nuclear, missile, and conventional arms-related activities. The order aims to enforce the UN arms embargo on Iran and limit its capacity to export arms to terrorists and acquire weapons for its own forces. The US has also imposed new sanctions and export control measures on 27 entities and individuals connected to Iran's proliferation networks. The article emphasizes that the US will not allow Iran to have a nuclear weapon and will use every tool at its disposal to prevent Iran from advancing its capabilities to threaten the rest of the world. It also highlights the need for the Iranian regime to change its behavior for the benefit of the Iranian people.